title: The Washington Post
comment: Resume at the start of Disney Donald Duck renewals 1966-JanJun
additional-note: The comics section of the Washington Post may include syndicated comics that were renewed by others (such as King Features or Disney), where the renewal does not specifically mention this newspaper (as the renewals for the Donald Duck strips noted here do). We have not yet determined when syndicated features with still-active copyright renewals started running in the newspaper, but it appears to have been somewhere between 1936 and 1938.
